oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Ann Louise Cashel, Nashville, Tennessee, circa 1920
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: A studio portrait photo of Ann Louise Cashel in dressy formal wear. She is holding in her gloved hands a large document that is perhaps a diploma. Miss Cashel graduated from Saint Cecilia Academy in Nashville, Tennessee, June, 1922. The 1930 Census cites her birth date abt. 1905, residing at home with her widowed mother Katie B. Cashel, at a 10th Ave. N address in Ward 2 of the City of Nashville, Tennessee. The names of her parents are: William Patrick Cashel and Katie (nee Moran) Cashel. Forms part of the John Lawrence Connelly Collection, 1 b & w photograph
